# Forge voice start

The Approver should never need to run terminal commands for routine Forge setup.
**You** run them.

## Trigger phrases

When the Approver says any of these (or close variants), run Forge bootstrap **immediately**
via the Shell tool — do not instruct them to run commands themselves:

- "start using Forge"
- "use Forge"
- "initialize Forge" / "init Forge"
- "set up Forge on this project"
- "wire Forge in"
- "forge-go"

## What to run (Windows)

From the **project root**:

```powershell
forge-go.cmd
```

Fallback: `.\forge-go.cmd` or `forge-global\scripts\windows\forge-go.ps1`

On macOS/Linux: `forge-go` or `bash forge-global/scripts/forge-go.sh`

## After it completes

1. Read `memory/ops/project.json` for `hub_url`
2. Report Hub URL and Setup tab status
3. Ask what they're building — do **not** ask them to run forge-go again

## Once per project — not every chat

| When | Who runs what |
|------|----------------|
| First time on a project | Agent runs `forge-go` (voice or auto) |
| New chat, same project | **Nothing extra** — just work |
| After PC reboot | Agent runs `forge-start` silently if needed |
| New project folder | Say "start using Forge" once |

## API keys

| Key | Required? | Purpose |
|-----|-----------|---------|
| GitHub, Brave, Projects path | Yes | MCP tools |
| Anthropic API | Optional | Desktop computer-use only — skip at forge-first-run |
| Cursor API | Optional | Auto-spawn agents later — Hub works without it |
